Version: 0.1.24
Date: 2026-04-15

Changes:
- Runtime structure:
  - split the CLI entry path into thin `index.ts` wiring plus dedicated bootstrap, runner, and sink modules.
  - keep REPL, one-shot runs, verify flow, and WeChat mode on the same runtime backbone.
- Tooling architecture:
  - add builtin tool catalog and tool pool assembly so runtime-visible tools are selected before schema injection.
  - add first-pass tool metadata (`source`, search hints, read/write and interaction signals) and route `tool_search` through that metadata.
  - make WeChat mode consume a filtered tool pool instead of the default full builtin exposure.
- Validation:
  - add unit coverage for bootstrap parsing, config resolution, CLI sink forwarding, tool pool behavior, and metadata-backed tool search.
  - verify multiple networked E2E scenarios against OpenRouter with `moonshotai/kimi-k2.5`.
- Repo hygiene:
  - ignore the full `bench/` directory in git.

Related commits:
- refactor(runtime): split bootstrap runner and sinks
- refactor(tools): add catalog and tool pool assembly
- refactor(tools): expand tool metadata contract
